The coalition of traders, artisans, market men and women in Oyo State on Monday held an emergency meeting in Ibadan to confirm the appointment of Alhaja Saratu Aduke Konibaje as Iyaloja-General of Oyo State. Alhaja Konibaje was the Otun Iyaloja-General to late Alhaja Wuraola Asake Kola-Daisi, the Iyaloja-General of Oyo State who died on Thursday, October 22, 2020. The appointment, they said, takes immediate effect. Speaking with journalists in Ibadan shortly after the announcement of the new Iyaloja-General, the leader of the coalition, who also chaired the meeting, Chief (Mrs.) Odunayo Kayode Danjuma said the decision was reached to move forward the activities of traders, artisans, market men and women in the state. “Confirming the appointment of Alhaja Saratu Aduke Konibaje as Iyaloja-General of Oyo State at this crucial stage of our economy in Oyo State couldn’t just be ignored if truly we are interested in moving Oyo State forward economically,” Danjuma stated. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state. Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report… [ICYMI] Lekki Shootings: Why We Lied About Our Presence — General Taiwo The Lagos State Judicial Panel of Inquiry probing the killings at Lekki Toll Gate, on Saturday resumed viewing of the 